  previewContent.problem_statement || '',
  previewContent.problem_statement_en,
  previewContent.problem_statement_zh,
  contentLanguage
)} />
```

Do the same for root_cause, user_perspective, engineering_framing, validation_thinking.

Also update the condition checks to account for both primary and translated content being present:
For `{previewContent.problem_statement && (` — keep as-is since the primary will always exist if any version does.

### Review sidebar — use pickLang on linkedFrame:
In the review sidebar where linkedFrame fields are shown:

Replace `linkedFrame.problemStatement` with:
```tsx
{pickLang(linkedFrame.problemStatement, linkedFrame.problemStatementEn, linkedFrame.problemStatementZh, contentLanguage)}
```

Same for `linkedFrame.userPerspective`, `linkedFrame.engineeringFraming`, `linkedFrame.validationThinking`:
